  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Young Offender Institution - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>

  <p>
A 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_young_offender_institution">Young Offender Institution</xref>
 is a 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_justice_organisation">Justice Organisation</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
A 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_young_offender_institution">Young Offender Institution</xref>
 accommodates young offenders between the ages of 15-21.  </p>
  <p>
There are two types of 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_young_offender_institution">Young Offender Institutions</xref>
:  </p>
  <ul>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_young_offender_institution__15-17_">Young Offender Institution (15-17)</xref>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_young_offender_institution__18-21_">Young Offender Institution (18-21)</xref>
            <p>.</p>
         </div>
      </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
For further information on Health and Justice healthcare, see the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_nhs_england">NHS England</xref>
 website at: 
    <xref href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/commissioning/health-just/"
            scope="external"
            format="html">Health and Justice</xref>
.  </p>

